<p><font>Perhaps an ironic reference to Spenser,
        <em>Faerie Queene</em>: "All night she spent in
        bidding of her bedes, / And all the day in doing good and
        godly deedes." - Volupine has been with Burbank all
        night and vainly displays her in her shuttered barge all
        day, trying to impress him (like Cleopatra).</font></p>
